page.title: 061ST MALBOROUGH BROWNIES
page.content: Every Tuesday{Brownies}is held in the {Church Institute}in{Malborough}at half past three.{Mrs.Cole}is{Brown Owl}and {Mrs.Day}is{Tawny Owl.}There are four {sixes}and they are called,{Gnomes, {Pixies, Imps}and{Elves.}There are {Sixers}and{Seconders}for each six. Every year the Brownies go on{Pack {Holiday}and we have four groups and four rooms (one group in each room).In the Institute the Brownies play{games and sing{songs.}At{Christmas}the Brownies go and sing for old people. We are both Brownies and we go {tracking.}We have songs at the start and finish of Brownies. We have {Brownie Smiles,}one of the Brownies has it for a week. At half past five we all go home because Brownies finishes then. Before we go home a Brownie says a prayer.
